.SH SHPowerL
Compute the power of a real function for a single spherical harmonic
degree.
.SH Usage
\f[CR]power\f[R] = SHPowerL (\f[CR]cilm\f[R], \f[CR]l\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]power\f[R] : output, real(dp)
Power of the function for a single spherical harmonic degree
\f[CR]l\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]cilm\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmaxin\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmaxin\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the function.
.TP
\f[CR]l\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree.
This must be less than or equal to \f[CR]lmaxin\f[R].
.SH Description
\f[CR]SHPowerL\f[R] will calculate the power of a function expressed in
real 4\-pi normalized spherical harmonics for a single degree
\f[CR]l\f[R].
This is explicitly calculated as:
.PP
\f[CR]power = Sum_{i=1}\(ha2 Sum_{m=0}\(hal cilm(i, l+1, m+1)**2\f[R].
